Class UbeeAPIException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable

    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NetworkUnavailableException, UbeeUnavailableException

    public class UbeeAPIException
extends in.ubee.resources.exception.UbeeException
    Exception wrapping the exceptions for the API. It decodes the results and throw an appropriate error. Generally is one of the following errors: UbeeUnavailableException, NetworkUnavailableException, UnauthorizedAccessException
    Can also throw RetailMapImageInvalidException, RetailMapsUnavailableException, InvalidFloorException, when dealing with maps.
    If any other error occurs, it will be explained in the Throwable.getMessage() method. Example: Wrong retail id utilized on a retail request. It won't throw a custom error, just a UbeeAPIException with a message notifying the error.
